NOTE FOUND INSIDE TERMINAL CASING
(handwritten, attributed to Ekko's modifications)

"Changed the encoding on this relay. Twice as hard now.

The old enforcers just did XOR and called it a day.
I added a byte shift underneath — add 13 to every
character code before you XOR it. Wraps around at 256.

So to decode properly:
  1. Base64 decode the output first
  2. XOR each byte with the key
  3. Then subtract 13 from each byte (mod 256)
  4. THEN you have the real message

The key is 7 letters. It's what powers their fancy
gemstones up in Piltover. They named it after the stuff
that runs through every Hextech device.

Base64 wrapper on top of everything. Good luck, enforcer.
You'll need it."

